<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <i><a href="http://projecteuclid.org/DPubS/Repository/1.0/Disseminate?view=body&amp;id=pdf_1&amp;handle=euclid.ss/1009212817" class="external text" title="http://projecteuclid.org/DPubS/Repository/1.0/Disseminate?view=body&amp;id=pdf_1&amp;handle=euclid.ss/1009212817" rel="nofollow">Scientific Method, Statistical Method and the Speed of Light</a></i>. Statistical Science 2000, Vol. 15, No. 3, 254–278</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPtolemy_and_A._Mark_Smith1996">Ptolemy and A. Mark Smith (1996). <i>Ptolemy's Theory of Visual Perception: An English Translation of the Optics with Introduction and Commentary</i>. DIANE Publishing. p.&#160;23. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0871698625" class="internal">ISBN 0-871-69862-5</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ptolemy%27s+Theory+of+Visual+Perception%3A+An+English+Translation+of+the+Optics+with+Introduction+and+Commentary&amp;rft.aulast=Ptolemy+and+A.+Mark+Smith&amp;rft.au=Ptolemy+and+A.+Mark+Smith&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B23&amp;rft.pub=DIANE+Publishing&amp;rft.isbn=0-871-69862-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Light"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
