<li id="cite_note-Rashed-4">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Rashed_4-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Rashed_4-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Rashed_4-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Rashed_4-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRashed2007">Rashed, Roshdi (2007), "The Celestial Kinematics of Ibn al-Haytham", <i>Arabic Sciences and Philosophy</i> (<a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>) <b>17</b>: 7–55 [19], <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017%2FS0957423907000355" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017%2FS0957423907000355" rel="nofollow">10.1017/S0957423907000355</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Celestial+Kinematics+of+Ibn+al-Haytham&amp;rft.jtitle=Arabic+Sciences+and+Philosophy&amp;rft.aulast=Rashed&amp;rft.aufirst=Roshdi&amp;rft.au=Rashed%2C+Roshdi&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.volume=17&amp;rft.pages=7%E2%80%9355+%5B19%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BCambridge+University+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1017%2FS0957423907000355&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Light"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>:
<blockquote class="templatequote">
<div>
<p>"In his optics ‘‘the smallest parts of light’’, as he calls them, retain only properties that can be treated by geometry and verified by experiment; they lack all sensible qualities except energy."</p>
</div>
</blockquote>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-MacTutor-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-MacTutor_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MacTutor_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MacTutor_5-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MacTutor_5-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MacTutor_5-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFO.27ConnorRobertson"><a href="/wiki/John_J._O%27Connor_(mathematician)" title="John J. O'Connor (mathematician)" class="mw-redirect">O'Connor, John J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Edmund_F._Robertson" title="Edmund F. Robertson">Robertson, Edmund F.</a>, <a href="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Al-Haytham.html" class="external text" title="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Al-Haytham.html" rel="nofollow">"Abu Ali al-Hasan ibn al-Haytham"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/MacTutor_History_of_Mathematics_archive" title="MacTutor History of Mathematics archive">MacTutor History of Mathematics archive</a></i></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Abu+Ali+al-Hasan+ibn+al-Haytham&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BMacTutor+History+of+Mathematics+archive%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Connor&amp;rft.aufirst=John+J.&amp;rft.au=O%27Connor%2C+John+J.&amp;rft.au=Robertson%2C+Edmund+F.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Light"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
